Pinch of salt and pepper

Tomato Cucumber Salsa:
½ cup tomatoes, seeds removed
1 cucumber
½ cup parsley
Pinch of salt and pepper

White Sauce:
½ cup mayo
1 tablespoon dry parsley flakes
1 teaspoon white vinegar
Pinch of salt and pepper

Directions:

Falafel:
Soak chickpeas overnight in a large mason jar in 3 cups of water. Make sure you only fill the jar with chickpeas about halfway—they expand! Drain chickpeas and dry completely.

In the bowl of a large food processor, add the dry, swollen chickpeas, garlic, onion, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

Pulse until combined and mixture resembles a small, coarse crumb. While the food processor is running, add the olive oil.

Get a 3" ring mold, or whatever you have around that will form little sliders, and pack the bottom with the chickpea mixture. Stuff with the feta cheese. Top with more of the chickpea mixture and press firmly. Gently remove the ring mold and voila! A feta-stuffed falafel slider patty ready to fry!

Heat ½" of oil in medium sauté pan.

Gently transfer falafel patties to the hot oil and fry on both sides until golden brown. Drain on paper towels and hit with a small pinch of salt.

Cut out rounds of flatbread with the same size ring mold (or invert a mug on the flatbread and trace around the rim with a knife). Pan-fry until golden and toasty. Set aside.

Pickled Radish:
Add sugar, water and white vinegar to a microwave-safe dish and nuke until sugar is melted, about a minute. Add the thinly sliced radishes and pop in the fridge until cooled. (The mix can totally last in the fridge for a couple of weeks.)

Baba Ganoush:
Prick eggplant with fork several times. Cover in two layers of aluminum foil and cook over an open flame on medium heat until soft and mushy, about 45 minutes to an hour. If you don’t have a gas burner, just toss it in your oven at 375º until soft.

Carefully remove mushy cooked eggplant from foil, scrape the flesh out of the skin with a spoon, and add to the bowl of a food processor. 

Add peanut butter, sesame oil, sambal, lemon juice, salt, and pepper, and puree. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool.

Tomato Cucumber Salsa:
Chop all ingredients and transfer to a small bowl.

White Sauce:
Combine all in a zip bottle and shake until combined. (This sauce is amazing, you can use it on just about anything.)

Assembly:
Drain radishes on a paper towel.

Spoon baba ganoush on half of the pita rounds. Top with radish, then crispy falafel, salsa, and another pita round. 

Zip with white sauce and stuff your face!

The Sandwich, what I used to, and still sort of do, consider the ultimate meal, it's got meat, it's got bread, sometimes cheese, it's easy to eat, delicious every time, glorious taste in every bite. 

I wanted to devise a video to show you 4 quick sandwich ideas that you can add to and play around as you wish in hopes of inspiring you to try something new and realize just how quickly you can whip up delicious meals with only a few ingredients.

Egg McMuffin

Ingredients 

English Muffin 
Egg
Canadian Bacon
Cheese

- Toast english muffins. Heat oil in a pan and crack egg into ring mold, and scramble season with salt and pepper. Cook Canadian bacon in pan. Remove ring mold and flip egg. Add Cheese on top of egg and add Canadian bacon on top. Sandwich between english muffins. 

"The Fact" (Flatbread, Avocado, Chicken, Tomato)

Ingredients 

Pocketless Pita/Flat Bread
Chicken
Tomato
Avocado

- Toast Pita/Flatbread. In bowl combine diced up chicken, tomato, avocado and season with salt and pepper. Scoop onto pita and eat!

Salsa Steak Tortilla Melt 

Ingredients

Corn Tortilla 
Roast Beef
Cheese 
Salsa

- Pan fry 2 corn tortillas in a oil till crispy sprinkle with salt. Heat roast beef in pan till brown, and add cheese till melted. Put cheesy beef on tortilla, add salsa of choice and place second tortilla on top! 

The Jelvis

Ingredients 

Cinnamon Raisin Bread
Nutella
Bananas 
Strawberries

-Toast cinnamon raisin bread, spread on Nutella and add sliced bananas and strawberries.

--

In this episode Josh thinks up the craziest cake in the history of crazy cakes. It's a savory cake with a nice slip of sweetness in it. This cake has a cornbread base with hot dogs in it, chili in the middle and covered in a mashed potato frosting and candied bacon, you'll just have to give it a try yourself, it's like nothing you have ever eaten before.

check out http://brothersgreen.com/ for all recipes and social media links! 

-Recipe-

Candied Bacon:
½ cup dark brown sugar
2 Tbsp maple syrup
¼ tsp cayenne powder
2 Tbsp apple cider vinegar
Pinch salt & pepper
1 pound thick-cut bacon strips

“Frosting”/Filling:
8 russet potatoes
½ stick unsalted butter, melted
¾ cup heavy cream, milk, or half-and-half, heated
½ Tbsp salt
Chili

Cake:
Cooking spray or oil 
2 boxes cornbread mix
½ cup masa harina (corn flour)
3 eggs
⅔ cup buttermilk
1 stick (8 Tbsp.) unsalted butter, melted
1 (8 oz.) can creamed corn
1 (4 oz.) can chopped green chilies
Cooked bacon, chopped
6 hot dogs
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese

BBQ Sauce:

These measurements are just an approximation. Just feel it out and add a little more or a little less of anything you like or don’t like. Have fun and experiment with the amounts!

1 cup ketchup
¼ cup apple cider vinegar
2 Tbsp grainy mustard
¼ cup packed brown sugar
2 Tbsp molasses
2 tsp chili powder
1 tsp paprika
½ tsp cayenne powder
½ tsp garlic powder
½ tsp onion powder

Directions:

Candied Bacon:
Preheat oven to 350º. You have to par-cook the bacon for a bit so the sugars won’t burn. 

Place bacon slices on a cooling rack over a parchment-lined baking sheet. The parchment paper really helps with cleanup! Bake the bacon for 10 minutes, flip the slices over, and bake for another 5.

In a small bowl combine the brown sugar, vinegar, maple, cayenne and salt and pepper. Mix it up with a pastry brush or clean paintbrush. 

Brush the par-cooked bacon with this mixture and bake another 5 minutes. Keep brushing the bacon every 5 minutes for a total of 40 minutes. Set a timer on your phone to help you out. This isn’t as annoying as it sounds and it’s totally worth it! Once your bacon is browned and crispy, you’re good to go.


Mashed Potato Frosting:
Steam the cleaned potatoes: Fill the bottom of a large pot with water. Once water is simmering, add potatoes to a steamer basket and cover with tight fitting lid or aluminum foil. Steam until the potatoes are super-soft and fork-tender--this can take anywhere from 45 to 90 minutes, it just depends on the size of the potatoes.

Once the potatoes cool down a bit, peel them. You can do this easily by rubbing a clean kitchen towel on the skin.

Transfer steamed potatoes to a large bowl and start to mash them up with a potato masher, wooden spoon, fork, or whatever you have around the kitchen. Once they’re mashed, add melted butter, warm milk or cream, and salt. Mix it all up and get it as smooth as possible. Set aside.

Cornbread Cake:
Preheat oven to 375º. Spray two 9-inch cake pans with pan spray or lightly coat the insides with vegetable oil.

In a medium bowl, combine cornbread mix, masa harina, eggs, buttermilk, melted butter, creamed corn, green chilies, and chopped bacon and mix just until combined. Add more buttermilk or masa if needed.

Transfer batter to the cake pans. Add three hot dogs to each pan in a triangle shape in the middle. Bake 25 minutes or until done. 

Top both cakes with the cheddar cheese and put back in the oven for 1 minute to melt the cheese.

BBQ sauce:
Add all ingredients to a small saucepot and heat until it simmers. Remove from heat and let cool.

Assembly:
Take one cooled cornbread cake and put on a big plate. Top with chili and mashed potatoes. 

Place other cooled cornbread cake on top. 

Cover the whole cake in mashed potatoes. 

Cover the mashed potatoes with the cooled, crispy, delicious candied bacon. If you want to get fancy, you can top the whole cake with a scoop of mashed potatoes and shredded cheddar cheese. Zip entire cake with the BBQ sauce and dive in!

And if you even want to take it a step further: Cut a slice of cake, heat a small pan, zip with oil, and fry/grill the cake slice. Zip again with BBQ sauce and party!

Quick Pickles 

Ingredients 

Cucumber
Salt 
Sesame seeds
Rice Vinegar
Sesame Oil

- Thinly slice cucumber and place in strainer. Sprinkle with salt and sesame seeds. Drizzle with rice vinegar and sesame oil. Mix and let it drain. Then Refrigerate. 

2 Ingredient Steak Marinade

Ingredients

Korean Gochujang Paste
Miso Paste 
Water

- In a bowl combine Korean gochujang paste, miso paste and a splash of water. Coat steak in marinade. Coat pan in oil on high heat. Cook steak for 3-4 minutes, flip and cook for 1-2 minutes. Take it off heat and let it rest. 

Sushi Rice (With leftover rice) 

Ingredients 

Rice Vinegar
Salt
Sugar
Water

- In a sauce pan heat up rice vinegar, salt, sugar, and water. Bring to a boil. Add leftover rice and mix. Put it into a bowl and let it cool.

--

A few great food hacks for that loaf of white bread you have laying around! 

Brothers Green: Eats! plays weekly in most countries around the world. Check your local TV listings for timing and if you don't have TV check your local MTV website to watch episodes and clips there! 

-Recipe-

White Bread Sushi
 
Sliced white bread
Deli meats (sliced, cooked or cured ham, beef, chicken, turkey or similar)
Cheese, thin-sliced—whatever kind you like 
Mustard
Pickle relish
 
1.    Cut the crusts off the bread.
2.    Use a jar or your hand to roll out the bread until it’s flat.
3.    Lay slices of meat and/or cheese on the bread.
4.    Roll that up and slice it lengthwise into four sushi-roll-style pieces.
5.    Garnish with mustard and pickle relish.
 
Instant Mozzarella Stick
 
Sliced white bread
Mozzarella string cheese, or a block of hard mozzarella sliced into sticks
1 can of tomato soup
 
1.  Cut the crusts off the bread.
2.   Use a jar or your hand to roll out the bread until it’s flat.
3.    Take your cheese and roll it up in the bread.
4.   Fry it in a little oil (canola oil, also known as rapeseed oil, is our preferred choice).
5.    Keep turning it until it’s golden brown on all sides.
6.    Meanwhile, heat your tomato soup directly over a flame (remove any paper label first!).
 
Dip your mozzarella stick right into it – you get the ooey gooey goodness.

Youtube - http://www.youtube.com/brothersgreeneats

Instagram - http://instagram.com/brothersgreen

Twitter - https://twitter.com/BrothersGreenBK

Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/BrothersGreenEats

2.    Use a jar or your hand to roll out the bread until it’s flat.
3.    Lay slices of meat and/or cheese on the bread.
4.    Roll that up and slice it lengthwise into four sushi-roll-style pieces.
5.    Garnish with mustard and pickle relish.
 
Instant Mozzarella Stick
 
Sliced white bread
Mozzarella string cheese, or a block of hard mozzarella sliced into sticks
1 can of tomato soup
 
1.  Cut the crusts off the bread.
2.   Use a jar or your hand to roll out the bread until it’s flat.
3.    Take your cheese and roll it up in the bread.
4.   Fry it in a little oil (canola oil, also known as rapeseed oil, is our preferred choice).
5.    Keep turning it until it’s golden brown on all sides.
6.    Meanwhile, heat your tomato soup directly over a flame (remove any paper label first!).
 
Dip your mozzarella stick right into it – you get the ooey gooey goodness.

--

-click for recipe- 

This pizza make look absurd, and for that matter it is, but it is gloriously delicious and a lot of fun to make, quite simple as well. All you have to do is prep your toppings, form the base layer, bake it part of the way, put the rest of the toppings on, bake it again, and then sauce it up and you've got a pizza that changes courses as you eat it. 

for all recipes, videos and social media links head over to BrothersGreen.com 

Ingredients:
Pizza Dough (from the frozen food aisle or get from your local pizza shop)
Breakfast​:
1⁄2 cup tomato sauce
1 tablespoon horseradish
6 celery leaves
1 teaspoon worcestershire 1⁄2 lemon, juiced and zested pinch salt and pepper
2 eggs
1⁄4 cup shredded cheddar cheese 1⁄2 red bell pepper, chopped
1 tablespoon fresh basil, chopped
Lunch​:
1⁄2 cup mayonnaise
1 tablespoon deli mustard
3⁄4 cup shredded parmesan cheese (reserve 1⁄4 for the crust) 1 tablespoon olive oil
2 teaspoon rice vinegar
1 teaspoon worcestershire
1⁄2 lemon, juiced
dash salt & pepper
1 cooked grilled chicken breast
2 tablespoons chopped pancetta with grease
1 head romaine lettuce
bbq sauce
Dinner​:
3 cups cooked elbow macaroni noodles 1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1 cup shredded cheddar cheese
4 pieces cooked bacon
1 jalapeno, sliced
sourcream hotsauce
￼￼￼
￼Dessert​:
10­15 cream filled chocolate cookies, crushed 1 pint strawberries
1⁄4 cup sugar
1 bag mini marshmallows
1 chocolate bar or a handful of chocolate chips
Directions:
Breakfast​:
Add tomato sauce, horseradish, celery leave, worcestershire, lemon zest, s & p to a food processor and mix until smooth. Set sauce aside.
Scramble the eggs with the red pepper and cheese when the pizza is in the oven.
Lunch​:
In a medium bowl, combine the mayo, mustard, parm, olive oil, rice vinegar, worcestershire, lemon juice, s & p, pancetta and grease and mix until smooth. Chop up the grilled chicken and 1⁄2 head romaine lettuce and add to the dressing. Toss to coat. Set Aside.
Dinner​:
Boil and drain the elbow noodles and set aside.
Combine sour cream and hot sauce in an empty zip bottle to make a delicious spicy mayo.
Dessert​:
Slice strawberries and toss in sugar.
Assembly #1:
Preheat oven to 375. Remove 1 wire rack from oven before it gets hot
Press out pizza dough on corn meal dusted counter. Use a rolling pin if you need some extra muscle. Press it out until it’s thin and roughly 14” in diameter. Cover the wire rack with foil, zip with oil. Transfer pressed out dough onto foil lined rack. Zip the dough with oil and gently rub it all over.
The idea here is to make a bullseye. It doesn’t have to be perfect, just leave enough room for each course. You have 4 of them!
Add a bit of bloody mary tomato sauce to the center of the dough.
￼￼￼￼￼￼
Outside of that, for lunch, add the reserved 1⁄4 cup parmesan cheese.
Outside of that, for dinner, add the cooked bacon strips and the shredded mozzarella cheese Outside of that, for dessert, add the sliced strawberries.
Par bake the pizza until the crust is just baked. About 10 minutes.
Assembly #2:
Add the scrambled eggs/red pepper/cheese to breakfast.
Add the tossed chicken salad for lunch
Add the cooked macaroni noodles for dinner. Top with shredded cheddar cheese Add the mini marshmallows and crushed chocolate cookies for dessert.
Put back in oven and bake until cheese is melted and marshmallows are toasty. About 7 minutes.
Assembly #3:
Zip breakfast with bloody mary tomato sauce, garnish with fresh basil
Zip lunch with bbq sauce
Zip dinner with spicy mayo, garnish with sliced jalapenos
Torch marshmallows and garnish with shaved chocolate bar or chocolate chips.
Cut up and invite all your friends over!

It may not be exactly how Willy Wonka would have done it but it's quite close.

Midnight Munchies, here to satisfy your late night cravings.

Check out BrothersGreen.com for all recipes and social media links! 

Monte Cristo Donut Waffle Grilled Cheese French Toast Sandwich

Turn doughnuts into a French toast waffle and add some savoury flavors to cure your midnight munchies.  

2 eggs
1 Tbsp milk
Dash cinnamon
Dash nutmeg
Dash salt
2 glazed donuts
1 slice gouda cheese
Sliced turkey
Sliced ham

Sauce:
2 Tbsp grainy mustard
2 Tbsp mayo
1 Tbsp honey

Directions:

Combine eggs, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a small bowl and whisk to combine.

 Dip glazed donuts in the egg mixture. Put one dipped donut on a hot waffle iron. Top donut with cheese slices and meats. Top with another donut, dipped side down.

Firmly press down waffle iron and cook until golden. Zip with sauce and eat.

Rice Krispie Treat-Stuffed French Toast 

Any time you have eggs and bread, you can pretty much make something awesome. 

2 slices thick-cut Challah bread
1 cup marshmallow fluff
5 eggs
½ cup milk
Dash cinnamon
Dash nutmeg
Dash salt
1 cup crispy rice cereal
Maple syrup

Make a slit in the middle of the Challah bread crust and gently stuff the pocket with the marshmallow fluff. This stuff is sticky; you can wet your fingers to help you shove it in there. 

Once the bread is filled with fluff, combine the eggs, milk, spices and salt in a bowl and whisk to combine. 

Dip the stuffed Challah in the egg mixture--make sure it gets nice and saturated and every part of the bread is covered. 

Add the cereal to a plate and completely cover the dipped bread in the cereal. 

Cook the bread on a hot skillet until each side is nice and golden. Zip with syrup and prepare to have your mind blown.

Today we are trying something new, I was rushed, I wanted to put this video out but I wasn't really allowing myself enough time to do it properly. Sure I could have ditched the video and done it again, it would have come out much better, look nicer and feel more complete, but f$ck it I say! Why not take a moment to show you guys what happens when a recipe goes horribly wrong and how to fix it and end up with some edible and hopefully delicious. Cooking in between the lines. 

INGREDIENTS: 
 • Pizza dough
 • String cheese
 • Pizza sauce
 • Shredded mozzarella cheese
 • Baking soda
 • Coarse sea salt

 • Stretch out your pizza dough. 
 • Place some string cheese all around the edge of the dough and fold the ends of the dough over the cheese and tuck. 
 • In a pot add water and add in some baking soda and bring to a boil. Toss in your pizza dough. Boil for 1 minute and remove. 
 • Sprinkle your pizza crust with coarse salt. 
 • Spread on your pizza sauce, top with shredded cheese and pepperoni. 
 • Back at 400 for 15- 20 minutes or until cooked through. 
Not pretty but pretty tasty! 


all music original by Josh greenfield

hIrZzSxMZU4.description:

Find recipes and more at our blog 📝 ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/blogs/all

--

(click here for full recipe) 

Brothers Green Eats! Episode 1 premiers on MTV UK April 28th at 9pm and MTV Australia April 30th at 9pm 

A visit to our hometown of Philadelphia inspired us to create this pretzel schnitzel sandwich. Soft pretzel bread with Vietnamese-banh-mi-style veggies, chicken schnitzel, and fried eggs sounds weird, but trust us … it’s SO. GOOD. 

Bun:
Water
Pizza dough (you can get this in the frozen-food aisle or from your local pizza shop)
1 Tbsp. pretzel salt
⅓ cup baking soda

Chicken:
Oil for frying
2 chicken thighs
2 eggs
1 cup panko bread crumbs
1 cup all-purpose flour
Pinch salt and pepper

Pickled Veggies:
½ cup white, apple cider, or rice wine vinegar
¼ cup water
¼ cup sugar
Pinch salt
1 dash fish sauce
1 Granny Smith apple
2 carrots
Daikon

Sauce:
¼ cup hoisin
¼ cup deli mustard
¼ cup chopped cilantro 
1 Tbsp. sriracha

Other ingredients:
Cucumber, sliced lengthwise
Cilantro
2 fried eggs

Directions:

Bun:

Preheat oven to 425°. 

Fill a large, high-sided skillet halfway with water and heat on high until simmering. Add the baking soda.

Gently roll the pizza dough into 2 sandwich-size loaf shapes. Add to the simmering water and cook about 20 seconds per side. Remove boiled buns with a slotted spoon and drain on a paper towel.

Transfer boiled buns to a parchment-lined baking tray. Carefully make small diagonal cuts on the top of the buns with a sharp knife. Sprinkle the tops with pretzel salt and bake for about 25 minutes or until nice and golden brown.

Pickled Veggies:
Add vinegar, water sugar, salt, and fish sauce to a microwave-safe bowl or a mason jar. Microwave until mixture is hot and sugar is dissolved, about 1 minute.

Peel apple, carrots, and daikon with julienne peeler or cut into thin strips. Add to warm pickling solution and let sit until cool.

Chicken:
Pound chicken thighs until thin.

Whisk two eggs in one bowl. Add panko and flour to another.

Dip chicken in panko/flour, then egg, then back in panko/flour.

Heat oil in medium sauté pan.

Fry chicken until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

Sauce:

Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.

Assembly:

Carefully slice open one cooled pretzel loaf with a serrated knife. Spread sauce on one side of bun. Add crispy chicken, pickled veggies, and cucumber. Top with 2 fried eggs, garnish with cilantro, and enjoy the greatest sandwich of all time!

Welcome to the cooking school where you will learn simple and creative dinner recipes that you can make in minutes! No more excuses keeping you out of the kitchen, lets get cooking! 

Visit http://brothersgreen.com/ for the complete video collection 

15 Minute Dinner Series - Asian Noodle Soup 

Ingredients 

Noodles (Dried Ramen, udon, buckwheat etc.)
Vegetables (I used sweet pepper and mushrooms) 
Scallion
1 Egg
1 1/2 Teaspoon Miso Paste
1 Tablespoon Vinegar 
Sriracha 
Soy Sauce
Sesame Oil
Honey

- First boil some water! Enough to cook the noodles and to have a broth, after all this is noodle soup! While you wait for the water to boil start thinly slicing your vegetables. Haggis is a traditional Scottish dish made with sheep liver and lungs and stuff. We made this quesadilla—using an iron—backstage at the MTV EMA in Glasgow, and we got Ed Sheeran, David Hasselhoff, and Youtube star Superwomen to Try it! 

Superwomen Youtube Channel 
https://www.youtube.com/user/IISuperwomanII

Haggis 
Chopped veggies
Sliced cheese
1 large flour tortilla
Sauce, whatever you’re a fan of

Layer haggis, veggies and cheese on one side of the tortilla. Fold the tortilla over and press down on the top. Wrap tortilla in parchment-paper-lined tinfoil and wrap foil around tortilla to make a packet. Press down on foil packet with a hot iron. (Sounds weird, but it works!) Zip with sauce.

4p3V0Zt1lyk.description:

--

(scroll down for full recipe)

Uncle Ricky swings by the loft to F%ck with Mike and spice up the classic ramen noodle packet. Will Mike survive the wrath of Uncle Ricky Ricotta? Find ouy now!

Ever caught yourself eating raw ramen out of the package in the middle of the night? That’s just sad! But this mouth-banging ramen-and-egg dish will blow your mind. 

-Ingredients-
Oil for pan
1 scallion, chopped
1 tsp. soy sauce
Dash salt & pepper 
1 package cooked ramen noodles + spice packet
3 eggs
¼ cup shredded cheddar cheese
4 sliced baby Portobello mushrooms (also called cremini), sautéed 
Ranch dressing
Sriracha ketchup

1.Spray oil in a small sauté pan. Add cooked ramen, form into a pancake shape, and cook till it’s brown on the bottom. Slide ramen out of the pan. 

2.Sauté scallion with salt, pepper and soy sauce in the pan. 

3.Add cooked ramen back to the pan, with the browned side on top.

4.Whisk eggs with the contents of the spice packet. 

5.Slowly pour beaten eggs over the noodle mixture and watch the ramlette start to come together. Flip it if you dare! 

6.Once the egg is set, top half the mixture with cheese and mushrooms.

7.Gently fold the ramlette in half and let cook another 2 minutes. 

8.Transfer to a plate and zip with ranch and sriracha ketchup.

-click here for full recipe- 

Make a cake in a microwave? It can be done—and it comes together in just a few minutes using just a few ingredients. 

1 ripe banana
¼ box vanilla cake mix
Water
Chocolate chips
Milk
Peanut butter
Coconut flakes

1.Mash banana in microwave-safe bowl. 

2.Add cake mix, then add water gradually, mixing until you have a cake-batter texture. 

3.Add chocolate chips and microwave until done, about 3 to 4 minutes. Invert onto a plate (careful, cake will be HOT!). 

4.Make the frosting: Put a nice fat heaping chunk of peanut butter in a microwave-safe cup for about 30 seconds, until just melted. Gradually stir in milk until you have a nice pourable frosting. Pour over warm cake and sprinkle with coconut flakes. You just made a microwave cake!

--

-click here for full recipe- 

Josh is obsessed with chinatown and came up with a crazy ass creation involving just about everything you can find in chinatown stuffed into one glorious burger. Check out this mouthgasmic creation!

Stick around for more recipes of our new show Brothers Green Eats! On MTV shown internationally around the world. Check your local MTV listing for show times and date. 

Bao Burger:
4 cloves garlic
2 fresh red chilies
½-inch slice fresh ginger
5 scallions
½ cup cilantro
¼ white onion
½ lb cubed pork butt
½ lb beef chuck
½ lb peeled, deveined shrimp
½ lb chicken thigh
1 wonton wrapper (for assembly, optional)
Parchment paper

Buns/Filling:
1 pork tenderloin
½ Tbsp. salt
1 Tbsp. 5-spice powder, divided in half
¼ cup soy sauce
¼ cup rice vinegar
½ cup ketchup
2 Tbsp. brown sugar
1 Tbsp. sriracha
½ cup molasses
1 tsp. sesame oil
2 thick brioche (or other) rolls

Veggies:
1 head bok choy
6 shiitake mushrooms
2 Tbsp. soy sauce
1 teaspoon sesame oil
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 Tbsp. rice vinegar

Crunch:
Duck skin
2 wonton wrappers
Directions:

Bao Burger:
1.In a food processor, add garlic, chili, ginger, scallions, cilantro, and onions and blend.
Add all meats and blend until you have a nice ground meat mixture.

2.Get your skillet hot and zip with oil. Form 3 thin burger patties on parchment paper. Flip onto skillet and cook until nice and browned on both sides. If you want to get crazy, put a patty on a wonton wrapper, fold over the extra ‘paper’ and fry up!

Bun Filling:
1.Preheat oven to 450. Get a large skillet hot, zip with oil.

2.Coat entire pork tenderloin with salt and ½ Tbsp. 5-spice powder. Sear in hot pan until nice and brown. Put tenderloin in oven for 20 minutes. 

3.Mix soy sauce, rice vinegar, ketchup, remaining ½ Tbsp. 5-spice powder, brown sugar, sriracha, molasses, and sesame oil in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, then let cool. 

4.Chop up pork tenderloin and toss in the sauce. Set aside. 

Veggies:
1.Chop up bok choy, shiitakes, and garlic. Add to hot sauté pan; finish off with a little soy sauce, rice vinegar and sesame oil. 

Crunch:
1.Fry up duck skin and wonton wrappers until nice and crispy. Drain on paper towels; sprinkle a bit of salt.

Assembly:
1.Heat buns in microwave for 20-30 seconds.

2.Make a small cut in the side of each brioche roll and gently stuff with the pork tenderloin.

3.Top stuffed bun with cooked burger patties, sautéed vegetables, crunch, and fresh cilantro. Zip with hoisin sauce and top with other stuffed bun. Now’s the hard part—fitting this mouth-bangin’ creation into your mouth!

-click here for full recipe- 

Check out our new show Brothers Green Eats! on your local MTV station for more incredible recipes and hilarious Brothers Green craziness. For those of you who don't get mtv or live in the states, you can watch most of the recipes right here on our channel!!! 

Mike once had a dream to combine donut and bagel to make the ULTIMATE BREAKFAST. So we made a jelly-filled everything-bagel-nut with sausage and egg scramble. Ladies and gentleman, THE BAGELNUT!

Everything Spice Mix:
¼ cup sesame seeds
1 tablespoon minced onion
1 tablespoon minced garlic
1 tablespoon poppy seed
1 teaspoon sea salt

Cream Cheese Frosting:
½ stick cream cheese, softened
¼ cup powdered sugar
1 tablespoons milk

Jelly Stuffed Donut:
1 can jumbo buttermilk flake biscuit dough
¼ cup jelly, whatever your favourite flavor is
Oil for frying

Sausage and Egg Scramble:
1 breakfast sausage link
2 eggs
Large pinch shredded cheddar cheese
1 scallion, chopped
Dash of salt & pepper

Maple Ketchup:
¼ cup maple syrup
¼ cup ketchup

Directions:

Everything Spice Mix:
Combine all in a small mason jar and set aside.

Cream Cheese Frosting:
Combine all in a bowl and mix until smooth. Add more powdered sugar or milk if needed—you’re looking for a nice, creamy, pourable frosting to dip your donuts in.

Jelly Stuffed Donut:

Preheat your deep fryer or heat oil in a deep sauté pan.You’ll need two biscuits. Press out each one until thin. Make a ring of jelly on one of the biscuits. Top with the other biscuit and firmly press the seams to seal. Make a small hole in the center and seal again. You’re making a jelly-filled ring donut, you get the point! Fry donut until golden, flipping halfway through. Drain on a wire rack. While the donut is still warm, dip it in the frosting and return to wire rack so the excess frosting will drip off. Sprinkle the warm frosting-dipped donut with the everything-bagel-spice mixture.

Eggs and Sausage:
Butterfly sausage and pan-fry until cooked through and seared.
Scramble eggs, scallions and cheddar with the dash of salt and pepper.

Maple Ketchup:
Combine both in a small bowl.

Assembly:
Top the donut with the butterflied sausage and scrambled eggs. Zip this beast with maple ketchup. Time to amaze your taste buds!

very excited to premiere our cooking show on on on @MTVBrasil tonight at 9pm!at 9pm!

INGREDIENTS: 
 • Ice
 • Salt
 • 1 cup milk
 • 1 cup cream or half and half
 • Sugar
 • Vanilla Extract
 • Pinch of salt

 • Fill a large Ziplock bag with ice and sprinkle in a bunch of salt. Close and mix it around. 
 • In another Ziplock bag add in your milk, cream, sugar, vanilla extract and a pinch of salt. Place it in the ice bag and shake it around for about 15-20 minutes or until it solidifies. TA-DA! Homemade Ice Cream!

one of the all time greatest fast food items... #6 at Wendy's 

Wendy's Spicy Chicken Sandwich

Ingredients 

Buns 
Hot Sauce
Lettuce
Tomato
1 Egg
Chicken 
Spices
Flour
(You may also want to have Saran Wrap for when you pound the chicken)

- First take your chicken breasts and slice them in half. Then take your saran wrap and place it over the chicken and lightly pound it (this will tenderize the meat). In a bowl crack one egg, pour in your hot sauce of choice and whisk together. In another bowl combine flour, cayenne pepper powder, garlic powder, cracked black pepper, and salt. Now it's time to bread your chicken. Coat the chicken in the four mixture first, then the egg mixture, and back to the dry mix. Shake off excess flour and put the breaded chicken in the freezer for better results. Heat oil on medium fire and fry the chicken for 3-4 minutes on each side, salt and drain on a paper towel. Now it's time to build your sandwich! Start with toasting your buns. Once toasted smear both buns with mayo, place your chicken on followed by lettuce, tomato, and your top bun.

On the Menu...

1:48 - Spicy Cornbread Pancakes with Spicy Syrup 

3:35 - Sweet, Spicy and Sticky Chicken Wings 

5:56 - Spicy Candied Cashews 

7:31 - Spicy "Tuna Roll" 

10:26 - Spicy Chocolate Brownie with Spicy Caramel Sauce


Spicy Cornbread Pancakes with Spicy Syrup

Ingredients

Batter 

Cornbread Mix
1 Egg 
Sriracha 
Milk 

Spicy Syrup

Sriracha Sauce
Maple Syrup 

- In a bowl wish cornbread mix, egg, Sriracha, and milk till batter consistency forms. Melt butter in a pan on medium heat. Scoop batter on to pan, and flip once you see tiny bubbles forming. Remove pancakes. Fry and egg. In a bowl (container etc) mix Sriracha sauce and maple syrup till combined. Top pancakes with spicy syrup and fried egg. 

Sweet, Spicy, and Sticky Chicken Wings 

Ingredients 

Flour
Chicken Wings
Garlic 
Sriracha 
Soy Sauce
Rice Vinegar 
Honey
Chopped Peanuts
Sesame Seeds

- Pour flour into a bag, add wings and shake up (you can also use a bowl to combine, the bag is just easier and you can just throw it away after). In a deep pan or pot heat oil on medium heat. Once the oil is hot drop in the wings and fry for 10-15 minutes till golden, drain on a paper towel (If your not sure that your oil is hot just sprinkle some flour into the oil, if it bubbles then it's ready). In a pan drizzle oil and fry some chopped garlic, add Sriracha, soy sauce, rice vinegar, and honey. Mix and reduce till thick. Add wings, chopped peanuts, and toss. Top with sesame seeds!

Spicy Candied Cashews 

Ingredients 

Brown Sugar
Cashews
Water
Ginger
Sriracha 
Sesame Seeds 

- In a deep pan or pot add brown sugar, cashews, and water. Reduce on medium heat occasionally stirring. Grate ginger, drizzle Sriracha, and sprinkle sesame seeds. Cook out liquid till sticky. Spray a sheet of tin foil with non stick spray, and let cashews cool. Place nuts in a bowl and enjoy!

Spicy "Tuna Roll"

Ingredients 

Spicy Mayo

Mayo
Rice Vinegar
Sriracha 

"Tuna Roll" 
Canned Tuna Fish
Celery
Sesame Seeds
Cucumber
Carrot
Avocado
Tortilla
Cheese
Spinach 

- For the spicy mayo combine mayo, rice vinegar, and Sriracha. Open a can of tuna fish and drain. Place tuna into a bowl, add chopped celery, sesame seeds, salt, and drizzle with spicy mayo to taste, mix. Slice a cucumber into think strips, do the same with cucumber and avocado. Sprinkle cheese on
a tortilla and microwave for 15 seconds. Top tortilla with tuna, cucumber, carrot, and avocado. Roll! Heat oil in a pan and dry the roll on all sides. Slice like sushi and top with sliced spinach and drizzle with spicy mayo. 

Spicy Chocolate Brownie with Spicy Caramel Sauce

Spicy Chocolate Brownie Mix 

1 Egg
Sriracha
Brownie Mix
Milk

Spicy Caramel Sauce

Sugar
Butter
Sriracha
Cream 

- Preheat oven to 350. In a bowl combine egg, Sriracha, brownie mix and milk. Spray oven safe dish ,(you can use cupcake tins too) and add spicy brownie mix. Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes. For spicy caramel sauce melt sugar in a pot, constantly stirring. Once melted add cubed butter and Sriracha, mix till butter is melted. Add cream, mix and let cool. Top brownie with ice cream, and spicy caramel sauce!

We've got a glorious one indeed today, Pok Pok's Famous Vietnamese Chicken Wings. Though most of the food at Pok Pok is Northern Thai food, they have some other specialities and these wings are a big hit at the restaurant. They also happen to be one of the easiest things (and with the fewest ingredients) to make in Pok Pok's cook book so I figured I'd show you guys my version. Enjoy and never forget to cook up a storm!
 

Pok Pok's Famous Vietnamese Wing

Garlic
Salt
1/4-1/2 cup Warm Water
1/2 cup Sugar
1/2 Fish Sauce (You can use soy sauce if you don't like fish sauce)
Tapioca Starch
Chili Sauce 

- Mince Garlic, sprinkle sat, and mince again. Soak minced garlic in a bowl of warm water. In another bowl mix sugar, and fish sauce (or soy sauce). Mix till sugar is dissolved. Then pour liquid from garlic into sugar mix. Pour half of the mixture into a bag with chicken. Let sit in the fridge for as long as you can (24 is best but 2-4 is ok). Heat oil and fry the garlic. Don't fry for to long (light brown a little colored). Drain on paper towel. Strain liquid from chicken and dry. Roll chicken in tapioca starch, shake off and fry in oil till golden. In a pan add 1/8-1/4 cup of sugar fish sauce, once it starts to boil and caramelize add wings. Cook until wings caramelize and sauce becomes sticky. Add in fried garlic and toss. Enjoy!

I wanted to see what it would be like to eat a Big Mac for breakfast and this is what I came up with. It is one heck and hell of a breakfast at the same time but it is oh so freaking gloriously incredible. You will marvel at the magnificent creation we hath doneith!

In this video you will learn how to create the Big Mac, the Egg McMuffin all at the same time while learning how to make the two into one sexified love child. 

Big Egg McMuffin

Ingredients 

Potato
Salt
Egg
Ground Beef
Canadian Bacon
Dehydrated Onions
Mayo
Ketchup
Mustard
Lettuce 
Cheese
English Muffin 

- Shred potatoes and soak with salt. Drain and squeeze liquid out. In a pan oil a mason jar lid on both sides. Press potato shreds into mason jar ring, fry, flip, and sprinkle with salt. Remove ring. In a bowl pour dried onions and add hot water to rehydrate. To make the sauce mix mayo, mustard, and ketchup (1:1:2). Flatten ground beef and use a bowl to cut meat into patty shape (using parchment paper makes the removal easy). Fry in pan, pressing down to keep thin. Fry Canadian bacon, and toast english muffin. Spread sauce on one muffin, then shredded lettuce, cheese, patty, egg, Canadian bacon, potato, sauce, dehydrated onion, shredded lettuce, cheese, patty, egg, Canadian bacon, and finally the muffin! Enjoy this super breakfast sandwich.

All music provided by Youtube.

--

I wanted to see what it would be like to eat a Big Mac for breakfast and this is what I came up with. It is one heck and hell of a breakfast at the same time but it is oh so freaking gloriously incredible. You will marvel at the magnificent creation we hath doneith!

In this video you will learn how to create the Big Mac, the Egg McMuffin all at the same time while learning how to make the two into one sexified love child. 

Big Egg McMuffin

Ingredients 

Potato
Salt
Egg
Ground Beef
Canadian Bacon
Dehydrated Onions
Mayo
Ketchup
Mustard
Lettuce 
Cheese
English Muffin 

- Shred potatoes and soak with salt. Drain and squeeze liquid out. In a pan oil a mason jar lid on both sides. Press potato shreds into mason jar ring, fry, flip, and sprinkle with salt. Remove ring. In a bowl pour dried onions and add hot water to rehydrate. To make the sauce mix mayo, mustard, and ketchup (1:1:2). Flatten ground beef and use a bowl to cut meat into patty shape (using parchment paper makes the removal easy). Fry in pan, pressing down to keep thin. Fry Canadian bacon, and toast english muffin. Spread sauce on one muffin, then shredded lettuce, cheese, patty, egg, Canadian bacon, potato, sauce, dehydrated onion, shredded lettuce, cheese, patty, egg, Canadian bacon, and finally the muffin! Enjoy this super breakfast sandwich.

All music provided by Youtube.

this is a mad mad scientist recipe for all you folks out there. We are getting trippy with liquid nitrogen and making my favorite dessert of all time, DIPPIN DOTS! It's fun, it's weird, sit back and relax. 

Dippin Dots
(Be careful when doing this!)

Ingredients 

Liquid Nitrogen
Ice Cream Base (I used coconut based ice cream)

- In a bowl slowly pour in liquid nitrogen. Take your ice cream base and put into a squeeze bottle and squeeze little drips into the liquid nitrogen. You can also use a spoon to drizzle in. Scoop out from liquid nitrogen and put into a bowl and enjoy!

original music by Josh Greenfield plus music from Youtube library.

osu0LqSsNek.title: 5 Ways to Get Creative with Pizza Dough
osu0LqSsNek.description:
Shop the gear in this video (and more) at ProHomeCooks.com ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/

Getting your kitchen gear from Pro Home Cooks supports more content like this. Browse below!

    ↪️ Small Appliances; https://prohomecooks.com/yqPg9O04

Find recipes and more at our blog 📝 ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/blogs/all

--

You can make it at home, buy it at the market, or even pick it up at your local pizza shop. Next time you get it, break out of the plain cheese pizza box and get creative with it! 

1:28 Pretzel Bites

2:51 Crispy Flatbread Sandwich

4:45 Stuffed Sesame Pancakes

6:40 Pizza Pockets

8:37 Cinnamon Rolls 

Pretzel Bites

Ingredients 

Pizza Dough 
Water
Baking Soda
Sea Salt 
Butter

- Preheat oven at 425. Roll pizza dough into a log shape, cut into pieces and roll. In a pan boil water and baking soda. Once the water starts to bubble add dough balls and boil for 1 minute. Drain on a paper towel. Spray tin foil lined cookie sheet a put dough. Sprinkle the top of each piece with sea salt. Bake at 425 for 10-15 minutes. Brush with melted butter and enjoy!

Crispy Flatbread Sandwich

Ingredients 

Pizza Dough
Lettuce
Creamy Dressing
Deli Meat
Hot Sauce
Cheese 
Onion

- Chop lettuce and mix in a bowl with creamy dressing. Flatten out a piece of pizza dough. Chop and fry deli meat in a pan with hot sauce. Then fry the pizza dough in a pan on both sides, top with cheese and let it melt. Add spicy deli meal, sliced onions, lettuce and fold over. 

Stuffed Sesame Pancakes 

Ingredients 

Sesame Pancake 

Pizza Dough
Soy Sauce
Sesame Seeds

"Stuffing"

Sausage
Soy Sauce
Honey
Sesame Seeds
Carrot
Cucumber
Spicy Mayo
Scallions

- Roll pizza dough till flat, and poke holes. Brush with soy sauce and cover with sesame seeds. Fry on low heat for 20 minutes, flipping ever 5 minutes. Brush the other side with soy sauce and cover with sesame seeds as well. Fry some sausage, add soy sauce, honey, and sesame seeds, caramelize. Cut open sesame pancake and add carrots, cucumber, sausage, spicy mayo and scallions. Close the sandwich and eat!

Pizza Pockets

Ingredients 

Pizza Pocket

Pizza Dough
Tomato Sauce
Mozzarella 
Pepperoni
Basil 

Garlic Butter

Butter 
Garlic 

- Preheat oven to 425. Roll out pizza dough till flat. Scoop tomato sauce onto half of the dough in sections. Top the sauce with a piece of mozzarella, pepperoni, and basil. Fold over the other half of the dough. Cut into sections (like ravioli). Seal the edges with a fork. Drizzle a cookie sheet with olive oil, and add pizza pockets. Bake at 425 for 10 minutes. Melt butter and crushed garlic in microwave for 1 minutes. Brush pizza pockets with garlic butter and return to oven for 5 minutes. Brush with garlic butter again and enjoy. 

Cinnamon Rolls 

Ingredients

Dough

Pizza Dough
Flour

Filling

Butter
Brown Sugar
Cinnamon
Chopped Nuts (Any kind)
Raisins 

Glaze 

Cream Cheese
Powdered Sugar
Cinnamon
Milk

- Preheat oven to 400. Flour your surface, and roll pizza dough till flat. In a bowl melt butter, add brown sugar and cinnamon and mix together. Rub filling onto pizza dough, add chopped nuts, raisins, and roll! Cut into pieces. Spray oven safe dish and place rolls. Back at 400 for 15 minutes. To make the glaze mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, and cinnamon. Add a splash of milk and mix again. Top your hot Cinnamon Rolls with your glaze!


Stay tuned for updates on our cooking show with MTV international coming out in April to 90 countries around the world!

--

welcome back folks! Glad to be posting again and this time we are doing seven awesome things with my, and probably your, favorite; BACON!!

All the recipes are super simple and a lot of them use part of one of the other recipes so they all sort of flow together. 
All baking temperatures for these recipes are between 350 and 400ºF
time to get crazy with the bacon!!!

Smoked Bacon Salt

Ingredients 

Bacon
Salt or Smoke Salt 

- Cook your bacon and chop. Put into a blender with salt and pulse. (If you want a more intense smoky flavor add smoke salt

Bacon Butter

Ingredients 

Bacon! 

- Chop your bacon and put it into a pan and cook down. Pour all that yummy bacon grease into a jar or bowl and let it cool down. Once it solidify you can roll it out into a log and wrap in saran wrap. Now you have bacon butter! (You may find it easier to chop the bacon when it is frozen)

Bacon Cupcake

Ingredients 

Batter-
(You can use store bought too)
Flour
Baking Powder
Baking Soda
Sugar
2 Eggs

Milk
Maple Syrup 
Vanilla Extract
Bacon salt
Cooked Chopped Bacon 

- You can use store bought pancake/cupcake mix if you want but if not...Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and eggs until smooth. Splash in some milk and maple syrup. Add a few dashes of vanilla extract and sprinkle in bacon salt and your cooked chopped bacon. Mix again and pour into greased cupcake holders. Bake around 350-400, and top with bacon butter cream (recipe below). 

Bacon Pancakes

Ingredients

Batter recipe from bacon cupcake. 

- Heat butter or bacon butter in a pan till melted and pour batter onto hot pan. Once bubbles start to form flip! Top with maple syrup for yummy maple bacon pancakes!

Bacon Butter Cream Frosting

Ingredients

1 stick of Butter
2 Teaspoons Bacon Salt
2 Cups Powdered Sugar 
Melted Bacon Butter
Milk or Cream

- In a bowl combine 1 stick of room temperature butter, bacon salt, powdered sugar, melted bacon butter and a splash of milk or cream. Mix till smooth. Top your Bacon Cupcakes with this sweet salt bacon butter cream!

Candied Cayenne Bacon

Ingredients

Bacon
Cayenne Pepper
Brown Sugar

- Mix brown sugar and cayenne pepper together and coat uncooked bacon. Place on a rack and bake in the oven (350-400) till crisp and dark!

Bacon Weave

Ingredients

BACON!

- Take uncooked bacon and weave together. You can either just bake the bacon weave as is or...Jazz it up a bit and wrap the weave around a can or oven safe mug, just make sure you spray the mug first so the bacon doesn't stick.

Bacon for everyday of the week!

n2MyYDNMF-w.description:

Getting your kitchen gear from Pro Home Cooks supports more content like this. Browse below!

    ↪️ Small Appliances; https://prohomecooks.com/yqPg9O04

Find recipes and more at our blog 📝 ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/blogs/all

--

Quite possibly my favorite ingredient to cook with, the creamy goodness of Coconut Milk can take so many food creations to the next level. Here are just a few of my favorites! 

1:20 Piña Colada Ice Pops

2:31 Microwave Coconut Cake

3:58 Coconut Curry Noodles

5:59 Vietnamese Pancake (Banh Xeo)

7:40 Coconut Rice with Mango

Piña Colada Ice Pops 

Ingredients

Frozen Pineapple
Coconut Milk
Orange Juice
Lime Zest
Lime Juice 

- In a blender combine frozen pineapple, coconut milke, orange juice, lime zest, and lime juice. Fill and ice cube tray and place toothpicks. Freeze!

Microwave Coconut Cake 

Ingredients

Shredded Coconut

Coconut Cake

Cake Mix
Coconut Milk
Water

Coconut Glaze

Coconut Milk
Powdered Sugar

- In a microwave safe cup (or paper cup) mix cake mix, coconut milk, and water until thick cake batter consistency. Microwave for 2 minutes. For coconut glaze mix powdered sugar and coconut milk together. Cut out cake and smother with coconut glaze and roll in shredded coconut. 

Coconut Curry Noodles

Ingredients

Bell Pepper
Onion
Chicken Thigh
Red Pepper Flakes
Cumin Seeds
Curry Paste
Coconut Milk
Water 
Scallion
Sesame Seeds

- Slice bell pepper, onion and chicken thigh. In a pan heat up oil, red pepper flake and cumin seeds, let it infuse for 1 minutes. Add veggies and cook for 5 minutes. Add chicken, curry paste, and stir. COok for 3 min and add coconut milk, water, salt, mix and let simmer for 5 minutes. Add rice noodles let it cook. Pour into a down and top with sliced scallions and sesame seeds.

Vietnamese Pancake (Banh Xeo)

Ingredients

Rice Flour
Coconut Milk
Water
Turmeric
Salt 
Mushrooms
Scallions
Sprouts

- In a bowl mix rice flour, coconut milk, water, turmeric, and salt till semi loose consistency. In a oiled pan cook mushrooms scallions and salt. Add more oil and pour pancake batter. Flip. Add sprouts, fold and drizzle with Sriracha.

Coconut Rice with Mango

Ingredients 

Rice
Coconut Milk 
Water
Salt
Mango
Sesame Seeds

- Wash rice. In a pot combine rice, coconut milk, water and salt. Bring to a boil then cover and turn to low heat. Cook for 15-20 minutes. In a bowl top rice with sliced mango (optional), sprinkle with sesame seeds, and a drizzle of coconut milk. Enjoy!

 
Stay tuned for updates on our cooking show with MTV international coming out in the spring!

- Wash rice. In a pot combine rice, coconut milk, water and salt. Bring to a boil then cover and turn to low heat. Cook for 15-20 minutes. In a bowl top rice with sliced mango (optional), sprinkle with sesame seeds, and a drizzle of coconut milk. Enjoy!

INGREDIENTS: 
 • 1 cup flour
 • Garlic powder
 • Onion powder
 • Cracked black pepper
 • Paprika
 • Russet Potato
 • Chicken thighs
 • 2 beaten eggs

 • In a large Ziplock bag add in 1 your flour and add in some garlic powder, onion, powder, cracked black pepper and paprika. Shake. 
 • Boil your chicken thighs for about 1 minute. Remove and pat dry. Season with salt and pepper. 
 • To your beaten eggs mix in paprika, onion powder, garlic powder and salt. 
 • Dredge your chicken in the flour and dip it into the eggs and then dredge in flour one more time until evenly coated. 
 • Fry your chicken at 350 degrees Fahrenheit until cooked through and golden brown. About 4-5 minutes per side. Salt to taste. 
 • Gradually add flour into your beaten eggs until it becomes a thin batter. Add water as needed. 
 • Cut your potato into wedges and dip your wedges into the batter. Fry until cooked through and golden brown. YUM-O!!!

wbNHT8W6X0o.description:

--

This recipe goes out to my younger self who loved me some Chicken McNuggets, man I used to crush a 20 piece with 3 packs of BBQ sauce. This is the closest clone recipe that I could recreate, there is something about McDonald's that you just can't ever replicate perfectly but this taste and feels just like the McNugget. Give it a try, so glorious! 

INGREDIENTS:
 • Ground chicken
 • 1 egg
 • Salt
 • Flour
 • Cornstarch
 • 1 beaten egg
 • 1-2 tbsp mustard

 • Mix your ground chicken, egg and salt until everything is well blended. 
 • Shape your ground chicken into nugget shapes. 
 • Mix equal parts flour and cornstarch and dredge your nuggets in the mixture. 
 • Freeze the nuggets until solid. 
 • Mix your beaten egg, mustard and 1 cup of your flour and cornstarch mixture and ½ a cup of water until it creates a thin batter. 
 • Dip your frozen nuggets into the batter and fry in vegetable oil at 350 until cooked through and golden brown. You can either dig in or if you want extra crispy nuggets you can freeze the nuggets one more time and fry for a second time until extra crispy! GLORIOUS!! 


Making homemade fast food freaking rocks! So much better than buying it out there, and you won't crap your pants.

--

When I first discovered the ultimately awesomeness of the Torta while exploring a Mexican food truck a few years back my life changed for the history of ever. Try this thing out, make it your own, use any meat, it's all about the combination of all of those glorious flavors.

INGREDIENTS: 
 • Sliced jalapeño
 • Vinegar
 • Sugar
 • Onion- chopped
 • Garlic- minced
 • Chipotle adobo
 • 1 can black beans
 • Steak
 • Flour
 • 1 Beaten egg
 •  Deli roll
 • Fresh queso blanco- crumbled
 • Tomato slices
 • Shredded lettuce
 • Avocado
 • BG Glorious on everything sauce 

 • Mix some vinegar, sugar, salt and a splash of water and toss in your sliced jalapeños. Microwave for 1-2 minutes. The easiest pickled jalapeños! 
 • In a greased pan, toss in your onion, garlic, chipotle and black beans. Allow it to come to a boil and turn heat on low. Add in cumin and salt to taste. Stir and mash with a fork. Set aside.
 • Season your steak with some salt. Dredge your steak in flour and dip into your beaten egg seasoned with paprika and salt. Dredge back in the flour one more time. 
 • Fry your steak until golden and crispy on both sides. 
 • Spread your black bean paste on your deli roll and top with fresh queso blanco, fried steak, tomato, lettuce, pickled jalapeño and avocado. Drizzle on some Brothers Green sauce. 
 • Fry your sandwich in a pan on both sides until crunchy. DIG IN!!!

k-RxKQsipwY.title: 5 Ways to Get Creative With Pancake Batter
k-RxKQsipwY.description:
Everyone has a box of it laying around but screw the standard pancake recipes and have fun with your batter. 

-- Menu --

1:00 - Onion Rings 
2:28 - Peach Ring Pancakes 
3:38 - Apple Funnel Cake 
5:22 - Buffalo Chicken Bites 
7:03 - Bacon Egg and Cheese

Find recipes and more at our blog 📝 ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/blogs/all

--

Onion Rings

Ingredients

1 Onion 
Pancake Batter (Bisquick Shake and Pour) 
1 Teaspoon Paprika
1 Teaspoon Garlic Powder

- Pour pancake batter into a bowl, add paprika and garlic powder and mix. Peel onion and cut into rings. Separate rings and drop into batter and toss. Heat oil on medium flame and fry rings for 3 minutes then flip. Once golden brown remove and drain on a paper towel. Drizzle with spicy Sriracha Mayo and garnish with chopped scallions. Serve with dip (blue cheese, ranch etc).

Peach Ring Pancakes

Ingredients
 
1 Peach
Pancake Batter
Pat of butter or Cooking spray
Syrup
Whipped Cream

1 Peach cut in half and sliced into rings. Spray pan with cooking spray or melt a pat of butter. Pour pancake batter to fit peach ring. Once you see bubbles forming on the pancake add the peach ring and flip. Caramelize the peach side. Remove and stack. Drizzle with maple syrup and top with whipped cream!

Apple Funnel Cake

Ingredients

1 Apple
Pancake Batter
Lemon Juice
2 Tablespoons Brown Sugar 
1 Teaspoon Cinnamon  

- Chop apple into chunks or dice and throw into a pan. Add brown sugar, cinnamon and juice of half a lemon, caramelize and remove from heat. In another pan heat up oil. Once oil is hot drizzle pancake batter into oil to from funnel cake. Flip till golden brown. Remove and cut into circles. Add apples then stack with another layer of funnel cake (build as much as you want). Top with powdered sugar and dig in.

Buffalo Chicken Bites 

Ingredients 

Chicken Breast
Pancake Batter
1 Teaspoon Paprika 
1 Teaspoon Cumin
Butter
Hot Sauce
Sesame Seeds

- Pour batter into bowl and add paprika and cumin, mix. Take chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces and tenderize. Add bite size chicken pieces into batter and mix. In a pan shallow fry chicken till dark brown and remove from heat. In a pan melt a pat of butter and add splashes of hot sauce, let it reduce. Then add chicken and toss till coated in buffalo sauce. Toss with sesame seeds and garnish with scallions! 

Bacon, Egg, and Cheese

Ingredients 

Pancake Batter
Bacon
Egg
Cheese

- First make a ring out of tin foil this will hold the shape of your egg and pancake (you can also use a mason jar lid, just make sure you spray it so nothing sticks!). Cut you bacon strips in half and cook to your choice of crispness! Then crack and egg into ring mold and once it starts to set scramble the yolk, and flip then cook and remove. In the same ring mold pour your pancake batter inside. Let it brown on one side then flip and brown again. Cut cheese slice into a circular shape. Build your bacon, egg, and cheese!

Sure you can take leftover pizza, pop it in the oven or microwave, and eat a duller version of the fresh stuff, but we wanted to have some fun and design really simple but creative recipes that would take your pizza leftover ideas and kick them right in the nuts, then say, hey nuts I have a much better idea, check it out, look what I can do. 

This video isn't meant to be followed exactly, heck no, it's all about challenging what you know about food, what you think it's limits are, and it's there to show you that limits and so called "rules" are meant to be broken. Go have some fun in the kitchen!

--

It's time to have some phun. You Enjoy Myself. 

INGREDIENTS: 
 • Cooked white rice
 • Cilantro- chopped
 • Chicken breast
 • Chipotle adobo
 • 1 Large tortilla
 • 1 Regular sized tortilla
 • Shredded sharp cheddar cheese

 • Sprinkle your cilantro into your rice and mix. Set aside. 
 • Sear your chicken and toss in some chipotle sauce. Add about ½ a cup of water, cover, place on low heat and until fully cooked. Remove. Shred. Set aside. 
 • Sprinkle cheese over your large tortilla and place the smaller tortilla over it. 
 • Layer on your filling, roll it up and grill on both sides. ENJOY!!!


www.brothersgreen.com

Parody of Phish's "Mango Song" 
song recorded and rewritten by Josh Greenfield of Brothers Green

Special thanks to Derek Lucci for kicking ass on the drums and rocking the bistro.

It just takes four ingredients to create this breakfast and lunch fusion! My favorite part about this dish is that you can eat it like a sandwich, maybe even take it on the go... 

For more awesome, simple and cheap recipes, unpredictable Brothers Green shenanigans and culinary surprises subscribe by clicking the link above, like this video, and comment with questions, thoughts, and ideas. 

Peanut Butter and Jelly Stuffed French Toast 

Ingredients 

Challah Bread 
Peanut Butter
Jelly 
2-3 Eggs
Maple Syrup or Chocolate Sauce

- Cut a thick slice of Challah bread, then cut a slit into the bottom. Stuff with peanut butter, and jelly then seal. Crack eggs and mix. Soak stuffed Challah in egg. Melt butter in a pan on medium heat. Once melted fry on all sides for 2-3 minutes. Slice on an angle and drizzle maple syrup or chocolate sauce.

The first soup I ever fell in love with... Seriously though, you cant beat french onion Soup, with all its melty cheese goodness! But with just four ingredients you can make it at home without having to buy any fancy serving bowls, just make it in a mug! 

4 Ingredient French Onion Soup

Ingredients:

Onions
Baking Soda
Salt 
Pepper
Beef Stock 
Bread
Provolone Cheese

- Slice your onions thin and add to a pot with some oil and a pinch of baking soda. Sweat them out! You want a nice brown caramelization. Season with salt and pepper and add beef broth. Rice crispy treats are delicious, don't get me wrong, but these things take that concept, kick it square in the nuts, say hello to my little new friend, and have their way with everything that makes living beautiful. 

Cinnamon Toast Popcorn Treats 

Ingredients

Popcorn Kernels 
Marshmallows 
Coconut Oil or Butter
Salt
Cinnamon

- In a deep sauce pan add oil and kernels on high fire. Use a mesh strainer as a cover and let kernels pop. Once popped remove. In a pot add marshmallows and let brown. Once it starts to brown add coconut oil or butter, salt and cinnamon and mix till melted. Remove from heat add popcorn and mix. Place on parchment paper and enjoy!

Often the best way to really get into cooking is finding simple and quick recipes that are delicious and fun to make. We have spent years finding the best of the best recipes that we think help anyone out there get excited about cooking. These are no hassle, no recipe, just get some stuff, chop it up, heat it up, mix it around, and enjoy. 




Instant Gourmet Pasta

Ingredients 

Pasta
Veggies
Sauce (I used Alfredo)
Parmesan

- Boil pasta in salted water for 12 minutes. Cut veggies at 6 Minutes and add into pasta and boil for remaining 6 minutes. Strain. Add back into pot with sauce and cook for 1 minute. Put in a bowl top with parmesan and herbs. 

Egg in a Tortilla

Ingredients 

Egg
Tortilla
Cheese 
Sauce

- Bite a hole in your tortilla. Put in a pan with oil and fry both sides till crispy. Crack and egg into the hole, sprinkle with salt and pepper, then flip. Sprinkle cheese and drizzle sauce! 

Chicken Veggie Quesadilla  

Ingredients 

Fresh Veggies
Meat (I used chicken)
Tortilla
Cheese

- Cut up fresh veggies, cook and add meat. Remove and add tortilla till crispy. Top with veggies, meat, and cheese, fold over and press. Cook 3-5 minutes till crispy and cut. 

Meatball Parm Sandwich 

Ingredients 

Bread
Meatballs
Mozzarella 
Sauce

- Heat the meatballs. Slice bread open and add fresh mozzarella followed by meatballs and sauce. If you want to add parmesan on top you can. Close the sandwich and press till toasted. 


Part one is great, but just wait for part two, a whole new set of recipes coming your way.

In this episode the boys whip out something that is truly the first of its kind. A creative and simple way to make homemade cheese slices. Best part? You can make any sort of cheese slices with this method, whole milk, and even non dairy vegan cheeses using almond, coconut, or soy milk! You can even flavor the cheese! All you need is some milk, whatever flavoring you'd like and something called "Agar Agar". You can buy it at speciality grocery stores or order it online. It isn't expensive and a little goes a long way. Agar agar is made from seaweed and is natural, and tasteless. 

Aside from cheese slices you can make cheese wheels and spice your cheese up by adding jalapenos, chipotles, hot sauce, or even mac and cheese powder! Go nuts, go cheese, go have some dang fun!

"Ballad of the Late Great Cheese Slice" 
all of the music is original and written, recorded and performed by Josh Greenfield

TsEyXJqB4vk.description:
Shop the gear in this video (and more) at ProHomeCooks.com ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/

Getting your kitchen gear from Pro Home Cooks supports more content like this. Browse below!
    ↪️ Pots & Pans; https://prohomecooks.com/j4JJovL7

    ↪️ Small Appliances; https://prohomecooks.com/yqPg9O04

Find recipes and more at our blog 📝 ➡️ https://prohomecooks.com/blogs/all

--

Banh Mi, a Vietnamese sandwich that is perfectly balanced and equally delicious. If you haven't tried one yet, be sure to go do so immediately. We put our own spin on it but the heart is there (even if we haven't tried an authentic one yet), it is the thought that counts, and by thought I mean the delicious thoughts my tongue has while it tastes this heavily creation. 

ALSO! IF you want to make your own ground meat but have no meat grinder, look no further. But what is that you say? You don't have a food processor either, no worries, you don't need that ish, I figured out a way to grind meat without meat grinder or food processor! First of its kind. 

Chicken Meatball Banh Mi

Ingredients 

Frozen Chicken Thigh (or Ground Chicken)
Garlic
Ginger
Cilantro
Salt
Pepper
Soy Sauce
Fish Sauce
Rice Vinegar
Carrot
Cucumber
French Baguette 

- Grate frozen chicken (or if you have ground chicken skip this). Chop garlic, ginger, and cilantro. In a bowl mix chicken, garlic, ginger, cilantro, soy sauce, and fish sauce. Form into meatballs and sear on all sides till brown. Once browned cover and let it cook through. In a bowl combine rice vinegar, soy sauce, and salt. Add shredded carrot, and cucumber and mix together. Cut open toasted French baguette, add chicken meat balls, raw cucumber slices, pickled veggies, cilantro, sweet chili sauce and mayo! Close and enjoy!

Recipe: 
KoKos Cheesy Chicken Taco Bowl with Ginger Guacamole 

Marinated Chicken Thigh
3 Pieces of Chicken Thigh
1-2 Limes
Oil
Salt and Pepper

Make a quick marinade for the chicken by juicing the juice of 1-2 limes and mixing that with 1-2 tablespoons of oil and some salt and pepper. Cut the chicken up into cubes about 1 inch wide and toss in the marinade. Cutting the chicken small will help it marinade quickly and cook even quicker so you can enjoy this meal with little prep and waiting! 

Allow chicken to marinade until all the other components are done. Once you are almost ready to assemble and rice is cooked, place a pan over medium high heat, add some oil, drain off the marinade from the chicken and place in pan. Cook for a few minutes, until nice and golden, on one side. Flip the chicken over and cook on the other side for a few more minutes until fully cooked. Take a taste, so good...

For The Taco Shell
Ingredients:
Medium Sized Flour Tortillas

Preheat oven to 350º F. Take a muffin tin, flip it over and press the tortilla in between the muffin tins to form a bowl with four points. Bake for 10-20 minutes or until golden brown and firm. Let it rest. 

Ginger Guacamole
Ingredients: 
1 Avocado
1 Tablespoon of Ginger finely minced
1 Lime
Salt and Pepper

In a small bowl add the juice of one lime and the minced ginger. Open up a ripe avocado and scoop out the flesh with a spoon. Add some salt and pepper and mix and mash with a fork or spoon. Taste, adjust seasoning and enjoy a deliciously surprising guacamole thanks to that ginger. Add more or less ginger to your liking. 

KoKos Cheeseland Cheesy Mushroom Rice
Ingredients:
1 Thick Slice of  KoKos Cheese
1-2 Tablespoon of Cilantro
6-8 Baby Bella Mushrooms
1 and 1/2 Cup of Basmati Rice
1 Cup of Coconut Milk
Water
Salt and Pepper

In a saucepan add around 1 and 1/2 cup of Rice. Pour in 2 Cups of water and 1 cup of coconut milk. Add in sliced Baby Bella Mushrooms and some salt and pepper to taste. Squeeze in a splash of oil if you'd like. Bring the rice to a boil, stirring, then lower the heat to a simmer, cover, and let sit for 7-10 minutes or until rice is cooked. If you are unsure, just quickly open the top, take a small amount with a spoon, taste it and see what it taste like. While rice is cooking cut the KoKos cheese into small cubes and finely chop up cilantro. When rice is done cooking, remove from heat, stir in the cheese until it begins to melt slightly, stir in the cilantro and let it sit covered until other components are done. Be careful not to eat it all before you are finished cooking because it is addicting...

To Assemble Cheesy Taco Bowl
Take a taco bowl and add the cheesy rice to the bottom. Then add a hefty amount of chicken on top, shred some extra cheese on top if you'd like, followed by a generous serving of the guacamole. Eat anyway you can, it wont last long because it is so dang delicious!

2MSq2IAw7Z0.description:

--

Ramen Noodles, while popular, can be pretty boring and repetitive... Well, not anymore! We are here to show you some awesome tricks to spicing up your Ramen Noodle experience, getting funky in the kitchen, and never seeing store bought packaged noodles the same way again. 

0:10 - Ramen Nuggets 
0:58 - The Ramelette 
2:05 - Egg Drop Soup
3:06 - Ramen Pizza 

Ramen Nuggets 

Ingredients:

Dried Ramen Noodle 
Flour 
Spice Packet (from ramen) 
Water
Chicken 
Asian BBQ Sauce

-Break ramen noodle into pieces. In a bowl combine flour, spice packet and water. Dip chicken into the batter then into the ramen bits. Fry in oil at 350, and serve with Asian BBQ sauce! 

The Ramelette

Ingredients:

Ramen Noodles
Spice Packet 
3 Eggs 
Scallions
Cheese

-First cook your dried ramen noodles by boiling, then drain. In a bowl mix 3 eggs with the seasoning packet. In a pan with some oil pan fry the ramen noodles on one side then add egg mixture. Let it set then remove. Chop up some scallions and fry. Flip the Ramelette over onto the scallions, add cheese and fold over! Enjoy.

Egg Drop Soup

Ingredients:

Instant Ramen 
1 teaspoon sesame oil
1 Egg 
Scallions 

-Boil ramen noodles for 3 minutes, then add spice packet and sesame oil. In a bowl whisk 1 egg. Slowly pour egg into ramen while stirring. Pour into a bowl and top with scallions! 

Ramen Pizza

Ingredients:

 Ramen 
1 Egg
Sesame Seeds
Asian BBQ Sauce 
Chicken
Mushrooms
Scallions 
Cheese

-In a bowl mix cooked ramen with 1 egg. In a pan with oil add sesame seeds followed by ramen egg mixture. Cook and flip. Add Asian BBQ sauce, cooked chicken, mushrooms, scallion, and cheese. Cover to melt the cheese. Enjoy!

-Boil ramen noodles for 3 minutes, then add spice packet and sesame oil. In a bowl whisk 1 egg. Slowly pour egg into ramen while stirring. Pour into a bowl and top with scallions! 

Ramen Pizza

Ingredients:

 Ramen 
1 Egg
Sesame Seeds
Asian BBQ Sauce 
Chicken
Mushrooms
Scallions 
Cheese

-In a bowl mix cooked ramen with 1 egg. In a pan with oil add sesame seeds followed by ramen egg mixture. Cook and flip. Add Asian BBQ sauce, cooked chicken, mushrooms, scallion, and cheese. Cover to melt the cheese. Enjoy!

For the caramel: 
Cook 6 strips of bacon on medium until semi crispy, take out bacon and strain oil in to a bowl. 
Heat 1 Cup of sugar in a saucepan (use a decent sized one as it will foam up). Whisk while the sugar melts, then when the sugar finally melts stop stirring and let it come to a boil. The second it starts to boil pour in the bacon grease while whisking quickly, immediately take off the heat and pour in 1/4 cup of cream, whisking quickly and bazing! you have your bacon caramel. Use butter instead of bacon grease (about 6 tablespoons) if you are not in to the whole bacon thing (but you should be)

Need some fun and creative ideas for cooking apples that go beyond the standard apple pie, apple sauce recipe ideas that have been pushed around for so many years? Check out this video and learn the top 10 new ways Brothers Green have created to help you use up them apples! How you like dees apples? 
Music by Derek Lucci - Bistro 
Dereklucci.com

1. Apple-Bons

Ingredients: 

Apples
Store Bought Cinnabon 
Frosting 

-Pre-heat oven at 375. Cut apple top off and scoop out. Stuff with store bought Cinnabon, and place on baking sheet. Bake for 13-15 minutes. Remove and drizzle with frosting and enjoy!

2. Boozy Lemon Apple Pops

Ingredients:

Apples
3-5 Lemons (juice)
Liquor (I used rum)
3-4 Drops of Food Dye

-Cut apples into bite sized chunks. In a bowl mix juice of 3-5 lemons, rum, and 3-4 drops of food dye. Stick tooth picks through each apple piece and soak in liquor for a few hours. Eat responsibly! 

3. App-O'Lantern 

Ingredients:

Apples
Lemon Juice 
Candle 

-Cut off apple top (save) and scoop out. Coat with lemon juice (prevents browning). Cut out a face and place candle inside. Light and cover!

4. Bourbon Caramel Apple Shots 

Ingredients

Apples
Whiskey/Bourbon
Gelatin  
Cream
Caramel Sauce 

-Cut apple in half length wise, and scoop out a bit. Combine whiskey or bourbon with gelatin and mix. In a pot mix cream and caramel sauce and bring to a boil. Once boiled add to whiskey/bourbon gelatin mix and combine. Pour into apples and let it set. Slice and now you have apple shots! 

5. Ham and Brie Sangie 

Ingredients

Apples
Brie Cheese 
Ham 
Mustard
Puff Pastry 

-Pre-heat oven at 350. Cut the top off an apple and scoop out. Stuff with a solid amount of brie cheese and ham. Top with mustard and wrap in puff pastry. Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes. Slice open and enjoy!

6. Apple Croissant Dumplings 

Ingredients: 

Apples
Store Bough Croissant Dough 
Chocolate Chips 
Brown Sugar
Cinnamon
Powdered Sugar

- Chop apples. In a bowl combine chopped apples with chocolate chips, brown sugar, and cinnamon. Wrap apple mixture in croissant dough. Pan fry each side for 2-3 minutes. Bake in the oven for 10-15 minutes. Top with powdered sugar! 

7. Apple Pop Tarts

Puff Pastry 
Apples
Reese's Chips or Peanut Butter Chips
Honey 

- Pre-heat oven at 375. Cut puff pastry into rectangles. Top with sliced apples, Reese's chips or peanut butter chips, and honey, then cover with another slice of puff pastry. Seal edges with a fork, and bake in the oven at 375 for 10-15 minutes. Drizzle with honey. 

For more awesome, simple and cheap recipes, unpredictable Brothers Green shenanigans and culinary surprises subscribe by clicking the link above, like this video, and comment with questions, thoughts, and ideas. 

8. Apple Bowlski 

Ingredients

Apple 

- Punch a hole in the top of the apple. Make another hole on the side of the apple to connect to the top. On another side make yet another hole as your "shotgun." Pack with herb of choice and light!

9. Nutty Butter Apple Bar

Ingredients: 

Apples 
Honey
Nuts
Chocolate Chips
Cinnamon
Peanut Butter

- Chop apples. In a bowl combine apples, honey, nuts, chocolate chips,  cinnamon, and peanut butter. Place on a cookie sheet in bar form. Freeze for at least 2 hours and enjoy! 

10. Warm Apple Pie...

A classic!

1 - Pizza
2 - Baked Potato 
3 - Egg in the Hole (bread) 
4 - Avocado 
5 - Quesadilla 
6 - Ramen Noodles 
7 - Biscuits 
8 - Fries
9 - Pepper
10 - Shakshuka

1. Pizza

Before your pizza is finished crack and egg in the center, place back in the oven at 450 for 4-5 minutes. 

2. Baked Potato

Ingredients

Potato
Cheese
Bacon
Egg
Chives

-Pre-heat oven at 375. Slice the top off a cooked potato. Scoop out some potato and stuff with cheese, bacon and top with a cracked egg. Cover the potato with its top and bake for 10 minutes. Top with chives. 

3. Egg in the Hole 

Ingredients:

Bread
Egg
Pepper
Ketchup

-Cut out of bite a hole out of a piece of bread. In a pan with oil add bread and crack and egg into the hole sprinkle with pepper. Let it set and flip for over easy. Remove and drizzle with ketchup. 

4. Avocado

Ingredients:

Egg
Avocado 
Bacon

- Pre-heat oven at 375. Cut avocado in half and scoop some out. Crack and egg into the center season with salt and pepper. Bake in the oven for 7-10 minutes. Sprinkle with bacon. 

5. Quesadilla 

Ingredients

Tortilla 
Egg
Cheese
Salsa

- Bite 2 holes in the tortilla. In a pan with oil add tortilla and crack eggs into each hole. Add Cheese and fold over. Once cooked remove top with salsa and enjoy!

6. Biscuits

Ingredients:

Store Bought Biscuits 
Egg
Bacon 
Cheese

- Pre-heat oven at 375. In a mason jar or oven safe mug add store bought biscuit, followed by egg, bacon cheese and another biscuit. Bake in the oven at 375 for 12-15 minutes. Remove and enjoy.

7. Ramen Noodles

Ingredients

Egg
Ramen 
Scallion

-Poach egg in cooked ramen noodle for 4-5 minutes. Serve with scallions. 

8. Fries

Ingredients

Egg
Fries
Bacon
Cheese
Chives
Ketchup 

- Pre-heat oven at 375. On a foil lined cookie sheet add french fries, egg, bacon, and cheese. Bake for 8-12 minutes in the oven at 375. Remove and add chives and ketchup!

9. Pepper

Ingredients:

Egg
Sweet Pepper
Bread
Bacon 

- Cut a pepper ring. In a pan with oil add pepper ring and crack and egg into it. Let it set and flip for over easy. Remove place on bread, Add bacon and ketchup and enjoy. 

10. Shakshuka 

Ingredients:

Egg
Tomato Sauce

- Poach eggs in tomato sauce for 7-10 minutes. Serve on bread.

4 - Avocado 
5 - Quesadilla 
6 - Ramen Noodles 
7 - Biscuits 
8 - Fries
9 - Pepper
10 - Shakshuka

1. Pizza

Before your pizza is finished crack and egg in the center, place back in the oven at 450 for 4-5 minutes. 

2. Baked Potato

Ingredients

Potato
Cheese
Bacon
Egg
Chives

-Pre-heat oven at 375. Slice the top off a cooked potato. Scoop out some potato and stuff with cheese, bacon and top with a cracked egg. Cover the potato with its top and bake for 10 minutes. Top with chives. 

3. Egg in the Hole 

Ingredients:

Bread
Egg
Pepper
Ketchup

-Cut out of bite a hole out of a piece of bread. In a pan with oil add bread and crack and egg into the hole sprinkle with pepper. Let it set and flip for over easy. Remove and drizzle with ketchup. 

4. Avocado

Ingredients:

Egg
Avocado 
Bacon

- Pre-heat oven at 375. Cut avocado in half and scoop some out. Crack and egg into the center season with salt and pepper. Bake in the oven for 7-10 minutes. Sprinkle with bacon. 

5. Quesadilla 

Ingredients

Tortilla 
Egg
Cheese
Salsa

- Bite 2 holes in the tortilla. In a pan with oil add tortilla and crack eggs into each hole. Add Cheese and fold over. Once cooked remove top with salsa and enjoy!

6. Biscuits

Ingredients:

Store Bought Biscuits 
Egg
Bacon 
Cheese

- Pre-heat oven at 375. In a mason jar or oven safe mug add store bought biscuit, followed by egg, bacon cheese and another biscuit. Bake in the oven at 375 for 12-15 minutes. Remove and enjoy.

7. Ramen Noodles

Ingredients

Egg
Ramen 
Scallion

-Poach egg in cooked ramen noodle for 4-5 minutes. Serve with scallions. 

8. Fries

Ingredients

Egg
Fries
Bacon
Cheese
Chives
Ketchup 

- Pre-heat oven at 375. On a foil lined cookie sheet add french fries, egg, bacon, and cheese. Bake for 8-12 minutes in the oven at 375. Remove and add chives and ketchup!

9. Pepper

Ingredients:

Egg
Sweet Pepper
Bread
Bacon 

- Cut a pepper ring. In a pan with oil add pepper ring and crack and egg into it. Let it set and flip for over easy. Remove place on bread, Add bacon and ketchup and enjoy. 

10. Shakshuka 

Ingredients:

Egg
Tomato Sauce

- Poach eggs in tomato sauce for 7-10 minutes. Serve on bread.

all music is original by Josh Greenfield

ingredients:
Roast Beef (about half a pound)
1 Long Roll
Velveeta or your favorite melty cheese
cut up onions

Heat up your pan or forman grill. Add a little oil and drop the onions on when it is hot. Cook onions for a few minutes and cut up your roast beef. Drop the beef on and cook with the onions until it just starts to turn color and heat up. Add the cheese on top, add the bun on top of that, let it cook for a minute or so, take off, and it is that dang simple! 
enjoy. good health, good munchies.

Chipotle's Chicken Burrito. How To Make Every Part. Other recipes on our youtube channel. 

Ingredients 

Cilantro Lime Rice

Cilantro
Lime 
Basmati Rice
Salt

Sour Cream
Jack Cheese
Cheddar Cheese
Tortilla
Chicken
Bacon Pinto Beans
Rosted Poblano Pepper Corn Salsa
Spicy Salsa
Guacamole

- Measure rice 1 cup of rice : 2 cups of water. Sprinkle salt and bring to a boil. Once boiled turn to summer or low and cover 15-20 minutes. Remove rice and mix in a bowl to cool. Mix in cilantro and juice from  1 1/2 limes. To make sour cream whisk sour cream till smooth. Finley grate jack and cheddar cheese (freeze your cheese or use very cold cheese). To steam your tortilla fold it and place in a damp paper towel, microwave for 30 seconds. Top tortilla with Chicken, cilantro rice, bacon pinto beans, spicy salsa, roasted poblano corn salsa, sour cream, cheese. and guacamole. Fold and roll, cover with foil.

Waiting for cakes to bake is a long part of a process that while can be fun can also be intimidating for the average cook. Why not start with some simple? Something delicious? Something that might even make you feel great....

Magic Microwave Ice Cream Cake

Ingredients 

1/2 Eaten Pint of Vanilla Ice Cream
Cake mix/Brownie Mix etc
Magic Oil
Chocolate Sauce

- Take a scoop out of your ice cream and place in the freezer. Melt remaining ice cream in the microwave. Then add in cake mix/brownie mix and magic oil, stir till cake mix consistency. Cut a slit into the cover and place back on. Microwave for 2 minutes. Cut out of container. Place scoop of ice cream on top drizzle with chocolate sauce. Enjoy, stay groovy.

DurblRo6w68.description:

Ingredients:
1 Pound of Ground Beef (80/20)
1/2 Pound of Ground Pork
salt
pepper
2 Tablespoons Fresh Chopped Dill
1 teaspoonChili Flakes
2 Cloves of Garlic Chopped up

Gently mix the meats together with some chili flakes, pepper, the garlic and dill. Form the meat in to small (or large) balls, sear on medium high heat until crispy on all sides, turn the heat down, add some BBQ sauce or stock, cover with a lid and cook for a few minutes until cooked through. Top with a pickle, throw in a mini bun as a slider, or just eat as is, enjoy!

This dish is simple to make, will impress your friends and may even get you a little something else...

Ingredients:
1/2 Pound of Medium/Large Shrimp Peeled and Deveined. I used 31-40 Count.
Juice of 1 Lime
2T of ketchup
1/4C of Mango, Watermelon and Avocado 
Splash of Cranberry Juice
Splash of Tequila 
Sprinkle of Salt
2 Squirts of Sriracha
Some Chopped or Ripped Cilantro if You Enjoy
Juice of 1/2 Orange
2T of Onions Diced Up

Cover shrimp in boiling water for 2 minutes, take out and immediately put in a bowl of ice water. 
Mix all ingredients in a bowl, toss around, taste, add anything you'd like, if you want it spicier add sriracha, if you want it to have more citrus add more lime, etc. 
it is that easy!
enjoy.

--

In this video Mike shows you how to properly give Parsley a haircut, how to debone chicken thigh to make it cook easier, and how to look sharp without any effort.

Ingredients:
2-3 Chicken Thighs
Parsley
Vegetable Oil
Lime
Garlic
Jalapeno 
Salt
Pepper

Debone the chicken thigh by making two cuts, one on each side of the bone and then a third cut from the top of the bone down to cut the bone away from the chicken. 

In a bowl toss in 2-3 garlic cloves, part of a jalapeno diced (the more the spicier), salt, pepper, oil, parsley and the juice of 1-2 limes. Add the chicken and either cover and let sit for up to 24 hours or wait a few minutes, and cook. 

Heat a pan over medium high heat, place in a little bit of oil and cook skin side down. Let it cook on this side, untouched for around 7 minutes to let the skin get nice and crispy, once it looks extra delicious and golden flip over and cook on the other side. If the chicken is on the thicker side cover the pan with a lid, turn heat to medium and let it sit there cooking through.
